text:
итоги 2018-го подвел instagram. за 2018 аудитория инстаграм достигла 1.1 миллиарда пользователей. самая массовая соцсеть в мире подсчитала лайки, хэштеги и геолокации и назвала главные тренды года.
⠀
😚 из них мы, например, узнали, что самая мощная фэн-поддержка сейчас у группы bts и вообще k-pop стал самым популярным направлением среди инстаграмеров.
⠀
📌 самым популярным флешмобом назвали #inmyfeelingschallenge, в котором приняли участие миллионы пользователей, включая даже суперзвезд типа уилла смита.
⠀
#хэштегигода: #metoo #timesup и #marchforourlives. в общей сложности они засветились в 2 миллионах публикаций.
⠀
👉 а вот и тройка самых горячих трендов:
⠀
3. эмодзи-символ сердечко. не то, которое появляется, когда дважды стучишь по фотке, а то, что просто ставят в комментариях. любовь победила с результатом 14 миллиардов. представляете, как это много? больше населения нашей планеты.
⠀
2. фильтр года. раздел stories позволяет нам не только оперативно сообщать всему миру о своих действиях. он еще и красивыми нас представит на раз-два. главным фильтром для таких самострелов стал тот, где на глазах человека появляются милые сердечки, а вокруг летают стрелы амура.
⠀
1. а тут у нас самое счастливое место на земле. знать это, как минимум, полезно, хотя бы для того, чтобы попробовать туда попасть и почувствовать себя самым счастливым инста-блогером. и таким местом признали…disneyland в токио. почему именно токийский филиал этой глобальной сети парков развлечений? просто под фотками с геотегом токийского диснейленда ставили чаще всего счастливый смайлик. а вы думали, как измеряется счастье в современном мире? только через смайлики=)
⠀

✅ главная тенденция: asmr
✅ самый быстрорастущий хэштег: #fortnite
✅ самое топовое сообщество: bts (#btsarmy)

text:
#napaunity day 7: solidarity ✊🏾 sigma strives to be progressive and encourages our members to stand in solidarity with the suvivors, the disenfranchised, the minority voices, etc. .
📍 lawrence, ks | our members of the alpha mu charter had the opportunity to meet, introduce, and listen to tamara burke, the founder of the #metoo movement at a talk on the ku campus. .
📍 washington, dc | sigmas at gw university wear black to stand in solidarity against workplace sexual assualt and harassment.
.
📍 albany, ny | our alpha chapter and sigrho at ualbany collaborate on a workshop to "break the silence" on domestic/sexual violence as a part of dvam.
.
📍 charlottesville, va | some sigmas at uva participate in a campus campaign on fighting the notion of apida americans being a model minority in the us. 
#syz #sigrho @sigmabetarho #napaunityphotochallenge 
#leadfromthefront

text_retweet:
a cultural debate has erupted over the classic holiday song, “baby, it’s cold outside,” after some radio stations decided to pull it — responding to complaints from listeners. the song — a holiday classic despite no mention of any holiday — tells the story of a cold evening with a man and woman, in which the man tries to convince the woman to stay (“baby, it’s cold outside”) and she repeatedly protests. “i think the song has always been creepy,” said lydia liza, a singer-songwriter. “but we didn’t have the words to explain why.” 📸: anthony camerano/associated press ❄️ what songs have you revisited in the light of #metoo?⠀
⠀
#repost @nytgender

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
the final addition to my #reverseadventcalendar for #staffordshire @womens_aid some @sainsburys free from mince pies! and that’s a wrap for my 2018 #robbosreverseadvent 🌟 this year i have been honoured that other women i know have seen what i’ve done and also put together a hamper for the refuge 🌟 .
.
.
a final word... at least 1 in 4 women  experience #domesticviolence in their lifetime. it can be physical, sexual, psychological or financial violence and includes forced marriage and so-called ‘honour crimes’.
.
.
🌟if you are living with, fleeing or recovering from domestic violence then the team at #staffordshire women's aid are here to support and empower you to move forward, to enable you to see yourself as a survivor.
.
.
.
🌟they will not judge you, or force you to make decisions.
.
.
.
⭐️it is important to remember that the abuse is not your fault, and you have a right for you and your children to live free from fear.
.
.
.
🌟their 24/7 contact number is 📞 0300 0330 5959 or email the national helpline 📧 helpline@womensaid.org.uk 🌟 #girlssupportinggirls #feminist #domesticabuse #womensaid #metoo #charity

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
årets juldrama i svt, systrar 1968 kretsar kring den nyutbildade journalisten karin (mikaela knapp). serien utspelar sig i ystad där den väldigt politiskt intresserade och engagerade arbetarklasstjejen karin fått ett vikariat på en lokaltidning genom hennes mors rådiga ingripande. 
karin får hyra in sig hos den familj som äger både tidningen och stadens hotell. familjens dotter ingela (anna åström) är dock till en början karins raka motsats, hon vinner fröken ystad och planerar det egna bröllopet. till ystad flyttar även karins vännina, konstnären lottie (maja rung). samtidigt som karin och lottie är självsäkra individer med stark integritet så är ingela osäker med en smula begränsad världsbild. men efter att ingela blir sexuellt trakasserad av en av stadens viktiga män hittar de varandra och de för revolten till ystad.

den politiserade stämningen som rådde runt 1968 genomsyrar hela serien med huvudfokus på kvinnors frigörelse. ett brinnande hett ämne även i våra tider. 
andra teman som tas upp i serien och som präglade 1968 är studentrevolter, fri kärlek, protester mot vietnamkriget och kulturkrockar mellan generationer, klass, stad och land. det fanns en gemensam kampanda och rörelse framåt vid denna tid som jag saknar i vår egen tid. 
serien belyser även till viss del dogmatismen och sekterismen som präglade 68-rörelsen. något som jag gärna sett mer av. även om jag tycker att systrar 1968 är en välgjord serie så hade jag gärna sett mer djup i den. serien är lite väl förenklad, polerad och grund ibland och jag hade gärna lärt känna karaktärerna mer på djupet.

på samma sätt som fröken friman tog upp kampen för demokrati och rösträtt som vi tar som självklara idag så har vi även 68-generationen mycket att tacka för genom kampen för kvinnlig frigörelse, abort, daghem åt alla, p-piller, fri kärlek och hemmafruarnas frihet. 
på samma sätt som spiondramat the little drummer girl, som jag tipsade om igår, frossar systrar 1968 i vintage, frisyrerna, färgerna, kläderna, tidsandan, bilarna och så vidare. läs mer på bloggen eller min sida på facebook. #systrar1968 #svtdrama #metoo #feminism #jämställdhet #svt #svtplay #tvseries #1968 #svpol

text:
2018
what an intense year. 
from losing 30kg’s, losing my grandmother who is and was my everything. to surviving some of the most challenging things that has crossed my path. some i have been very vocal about, some not so much. from losing chances for love, to making wrong decisions. i am proud to say, 2018 has not broken me. and nothing will. every challenge that came my way, i had the option of throwing in the rope like previously. but i am better, stronger and more confident than ever. i want to take this opportunity to thank every single friend and family member for always being there. thank you. 
i can only try and motivate the next person, with experiences i’ve had over the years and the most important life hack i’ve learnt this year - everything in life is a choice. some might not agree, some might. being ugly - is a choice - being weak - is a choice. being poor, is a choice! being unhappy in a recurring situation- is a choice! 
choose to focus on yourself in 2019, set your goals. choose to be happy. choose you. 
don’t ever give up. 
happy almost new year! ♥️ #motivationalquotes #motivation #weightloss #suicide #metoo #crashing #empowerment #goodbye #nevergiveup #loveyourlife #loveyourself #youcandothis #gay22 #gaylife #gayproblems #hair #fitness

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
fight like a girl || slapping someone with weak wrists.❌
_______________________________________________________________________
fight like a girl || to never give up, never back down. to stay optimistic in the face of adversity. be true to yourself, even when those around you may doubt what you're doing. sometimes the ones we love can, unintentionally, project their own fears onto others in hopes of protecting them. follow your intuition, it's a very powerful ally. and if you don't have keen intuition then get into the practice of quieting down your mind so you can listen. fighting like a girl means you don't let your circumstance define you. you defy it, you empower yourself, you use the circumstance as an opportunity for growth and not as a casting call to play the role of victim. this doesn't mean you go completely numb. there are going to be days when you need to cry, you need to break things, scream, eat that bowl (eh hem, not pint) of ice-cream, call that friend or relative and tell them how miserable you are that things have changed in your life so drastically.

fight like a girl || to never give up, never back down. to stay optimistic in the face of adversity. be true to yourself, even when those around you may doubt what you are doing. sometimes the ones we love can, unintentionally, project their own fears onto others in hopes of protecting them. follow your intuition, it is a very powerful ally. and if you do not have keen intuition then get into the practice of quieting down your mind so you can listen. fighting like a girl means you do not let your circumstance define you. you defy it, you empower yourself, you use the circumstance as an opportunity for growth and not as a casting call to play the role of victim. this does not mean you go completely numb. there are going to be days when you need to cry, you need to break things, scream, eat that bowl (eh hem, not pint) of ice-cream, call that friend or relative and tell them how miserable you are that things have changed in your life so drastically.

text:
las mujeres de los balcanes rompieron su silencio para contar los sufrimientos vividos en las salas de maternidad, un fenómeno que se asemeja al movimiento antiacoso #metoo, con poco eco entre las sociedades conservadoras de la región. 
lanzada en croacia hace algunos años, una campaña animaba a las mujeres a contar sus experiencias, pero fue el testimonio reciente de una diputada lo que incitó un movimiento que se extendió también a los países vecinos.

esta parlamentaria, ivana nincevic-lesandric, conmocionó a sus pares al narrar, en la asamblea nacional, detalles muy íntimos sobre su “trauma”.después de haber sufrido un aborto espontáneo, se dirigió a un hospital público de split (sur). “era el siglo xv […] ataron mis brazos y mis piernas y comenzaron el legrado sin anestesia […] fueron los treinta minutos más horribles de mi vida”, contó en octubre esta diputada de 35 años ante una asamblea dominada por hombres.

#ciencia #maternidad #croacia

esta parlamentaria, ivana nincevic-lesandric, conmocionó a sus pares al narrar, en la asamblea nacional, detalles muy íntimos sobre su “trauma”.después de haber sufrido un aboo espontáneo, se dirigió a un hospital público de split (sur). “era el siglo xv […] ataron mis brazos y mis piernas y comenzaron el legrado sin anestesia […] fueron los treinta minutos más horribles de mi vida”, contó en octubre esta diputada de 35 años ante una asamblea dominada por hombres.

text:
this morning i committed a mortal sin apparently. in an honest mistake i credited a photo to the wrong person, for which i received a sarcastic, childish reply for. when i realised my mistake i immediately corrected it, and gave the photographer a bit of his own medicine back. i've had a number of dms supporting me for standing up to him as they could clearly see i had made an honest mistake and did the right thing as soon as i knew. anyone who is a regular 'reader' of my posts knows that, i always where possible, credit a person's work. 
sadly this particular precious little petal seems to have a bit of an issue with his eq, because after immediately doing what he asked of me ie crediting him for the photo he still went on. unfortunately for him, numerous people seen it and weren't impressed with his attitude so he's lost potential clientele through his own actions. they will no doubt tell a few more......etc etc etc.

i forgive him. he obviously needs to do some work on his ego, get down off that pedastal he's put himself on and pull his head out of his arse: because here's a  newsflash - the sun doesn't revolve around him and nor does ig. that's exactly how he came across today to numerous people and i ended up receiving more followers from it. not because i did anything wonderful. i simply stood up to a male who thought he could bully me. that doesn't work in this day and age. it especially doesn't go down well since the #metoo movement began.

if i ever make a mistake in crediting the wrong person for a piece of work, a polite dm to me will have the situation resolved as soon as i see it, but don't for one minute think that you're going to suddenly appear on my page with bullying and sarcastic comments, and get away with your rubbish. i don't like conflict at all but i give as good as i get.

finally please let me say how thankful i am for my authentic genuine contacts/followers. thankfully my 'tribe' doesn't consist of any precious or precocious little petals and they have talent and intestinal fortitude and then some. thank you for your words of support today. it's all good. karma's a bitch.

text:
you’d be forgiven for feeling like 2018 was a bit of a blur; a lot has happened over the past 12 months, so to help gain some clarity, we’ll be revisiting moments that had an impact on our world. let’s start with the @timesupnow protest at the golden globes, where 300 women turned up in black to protest sexual harassment in us workplaces. the campaign was launched as a companion to the #metoo movement and has raised more than $20m in legal defence funds primarily used to fight sexual misconduct cases brought by low-paid workers. the fund's co-founder, roberta kaplan, said the movement as a whole is encouraging thousands of women to “come out” as victims of misconduct. “i think it’s revolutionary and it’s not going to go back. i can’t see women agreeing to return to the days of isolation and shame.” #thiswas2018

photos: frazer harrison + matthias nareyek + jonny birch + mario anzuoni + stephane cardinale + paul sancya + spencer platt

text:
to all the writers like me
i see you
walking away from
pain all day
only to return to it's lap
as dawn transcends into dusk.

i see you
finding comfort in darkness
the same kind you found in
dad's arms once,
while the entire world 
scorns
at your eccentricity.

i see you
direly trying to hide
your poems from ma
in the fear of seeing her 
crash to the ground
with dilemma ridden eyes
seeing her burn those sheets
like it was your pyre

i see you
endlessly lying about
why you write
confusing passion with ache
when it is the only thing
keeping you alive.

i see you
i see your heart break
into two
as you soak words
with blood
and sponge the yellow walls
of your room
you don't  know
when you fell in love
with spilling blood
instead of it flowing through your veins.

i see you
every night
as you pick up the quill
and wonder
why do you relate to plath more
when wordsworth 
was the one
who wrote happier poems.
you eat black for breakfast 
and bukowski's melancholy for lunch
while emptiness fills your stomach
before you sleep.

i see you
not sleep
but write that
emptiness away
so that you wake up
looking full the next day
so that the world
doesn't question
the void in your eyes
and that lack of light.

i see you
and i know 
you see me
so can we just spend
one evening 
aching together 
not smiling or laughing.
one evening where 
we are not faced with the
brunt of explaining 
this overwhelming numbness.
one evening where we
analyse why our poems don't rhyme anymore
as darkness lulls us to sleep.
till that one evening,
i will continue seeing you
from the corner
quietly.
.
.
arunima sengupta.
(@adding_soul_to_words)
.
.

text:
@the.asian.feminist is now on @medium! in our first blog, we look back at several events in 2018: how women survivors in asia are failed by their countries’ legal system. we write:
‘dictionary merriam-webster has chosen “justice” as the word of the year 2018, saying it was the website’s top lookup of the year. with this news, we should reflect on how justice has materialized for women in asia, especially those who experience gender-based violence. the answer is unfortunately not encouraging. recent court cases, from malaysia to indonesia, from hong kong to china, highlight that the legal system not only fails to protect but also is very hostile and punitive toward women survivors.’ we look at baiq nuril maknun’s case in indonesia, a #dv survivor who was denied divorce in china, an abused mother who was punished for raising domestic violence in hong kong’s family court and others. 
special thanks to @monaeltahawy whose reference to judith herman and her powerful quote is very useful to this essay, and prof #katemanne who coined the term “himpathy”. dedicated to all women survivors out there. link in bio. 
#vaw #gbv #metoo #dv #domesticviolence #sexualharassment #sexualassault

text:
dr. christine blasey ford was at one point of the year the most talked about woman in the world. she bravely gave up her anonymity to publicly accuse brett kavanaugh of sexual assault. in response to her statement of her ordeal she has been the publicly mocked and ridiculed (including by president trump himself) as well as the assault itself deemed by some as too trivial. her personal and family’s security was also at risk by death threats with them having to move house. with all of this kavanaugh was narrowly voted onto and sworn onto the supreme court - the highest court in the federal judiciary of the united states. 
dr. blasey ford’s public statement has had a lastly impact, not perhaps on kavanaugh, but on everyone who has ever been the victim of sexual assault. she has given those a voice, the bravery to speak up, and has brought the conversation of consent to the forefront. 
thank you dr. blasey ford for your calmness and courage in the face of all you have faced.

#shero #hero #equalrights #drblaseyford #feminist #metoo #speakup #fff

text_retweet:
reposted from @beyond_thoughtss -  to all the writers like me
i see you
walking away from
pain all day
only to return to it's lap
as dawn transcends into dusk.

i see you
finding comfort in darkness
the same kind you found in
dad's arms once,
while the entire world 
scorns
at your eccentricity.

i see you
direly trying to hide
your poems from ma
in the fear of seeing her 
crash to the ground
with dilemma ridden eyes
seeing her burn those sheets
like it was your pyre

i see you
endlessly lying about
why you write
confusing passion with ache
when it is the only thing
keeping you alive.

i see you
i see your heart break
into two
as you soak words
with blood
and sponge the yellow walls
of your room
you don't  know
when you fell in love
with spilling blood
instead of it flowing through your veins.

i see you
every night
as you pick up the quill
and wonder
why do you relate to plath more
when wordsworth 
was the one
who wrote happier poems.
you eat black for breakfast 
and bukowski's melancholy for lunch
while emptiness fills your stomach
before you sleep.

i see you
not sleep
but write that
emptiness away
so that you wake up
looking full the next day
so that the world
doesn't question
the void in your eyes
and that lack of light.

i see you
and i know 
you see me
so can we just spend
one evening 
aching together 
not smiling or laughing.
one evening where 
we are not faced with the
brunt of explaining 
this overwhelming numbness.
one evening where we
analyse why our poems don't rhyme anymore
as darkness lulls us to sleep.
till that one evening,
i will continue seeing you
from the corner
quietly.
.
.
arunima sengupta.
(@adding_soul_to_words)
.
.

text:
with the new year upon us, 
we take some time to look back through some of our highlights of 2018 with gratitude, optimism and humility. we are so grateful 
to have had such a beautiful 2018 and we owe it to our muses, supporters, partners, employees and all of you, who believe in us. 
we begin our memories of 2018 with the watershed golden globes, an award carpet and ceremony marked by the collective strength of so many women who joined together to use fashion as a protest, a visual language against the injustices faced as survivors of, and in support of the survivors of the #metoo movement. we are proud to have dressed two muses—  golden globe nominee @issarae in atelier prabal gurung and @kerrywashington in a special look straight from our newest collection. both looks were auctioned off to benefit @timesupnow in support for this moment of resistance, resilience and unity.
#pgworld #pgmuse #beautywithsubstance #femininitywithabite #modernglamour #luxurywithsoul

text:
day 1: management mantra 2018@scwbgn

with the blessings of the almighty, day 1 of management mantra witnessed events like *let's talk (a ted talk show)* where the students *talked about gender equality, self motivation, traveling* etc.
*symposium* witnessed a heated *discussion about #metoo* whereas *business plan competition* put forth various products and services that would make our life a better one.
last but not the least, the *students of science department have exhibited 12 under the model-making competition*.
the honourable judges felt extremely delighted to see such marvels and have already provided *an opportunity to exhibit the same at institute of science, bhu*.

text:
서지현 검사의 미투가 터지고 얼마 뒤 나는 한 검사의 저자 강연회에 참석했다.
당연히 이번 미투에 대해 어떻게 생각하냐는 질문이 나왔다.
그는 이렇게 대답했다.
.
"백번 잘못한 일이고, 저희 검사 조직이 반성해야해요.
그런데 솔직히 국민들이 너무 검사 집단을 과도하게 공격하는 것 같아요. 저희도 다른 집단과 다를 거 없거든요."
.
그 말을 들었을 때 나는 주위를 둘러봤다.
작은 실내에 그의 후배들이 자리를 채우고 있었다.
그때의 나의 기분, 나의 좌절, 나의 실망, 사회자의 표정을
아직도 잊을 수 없다.
나는 한 마디도 할 수 없었다.
그날 이후로 나는 서지현 검사에게 부채감을 느낀다.
.
올해의 인물,  서지현 검사.
#시사in 과 #주간경향  선정
.
2018년은 나의 #젠더 관념이 급변한 해였다. 나뿐만 아니라 모두가 그럴 것이다.
대체로 #성폭력 의 피해자였던 내가 가해자 또한 될 수 있다는 강렬한 깨달음을 얻은 것이 가장 큰 수확이다.
올해는 한국형 권력과 젠더 문제의 혼합이 가져온 혼란 속에 내 의견을 정립하는 것조차 어려웠다.
이런 혼란이 긍정적인 토론과 합의의 장으로 나아간다면 더없이 좋을텐데 말이다.
.
이런 난리통에 서로 조심하는 분위기가 생겨났다지만
며칠 전에도 나는 여자애답지 못한 복장과 헤어스타일을 상사에게 지적받았다.
"여자는 사회 생활할 때 예쁘게 하고 다녀야해. 넌 여자애가 그게 뭐니. 그 머리를 하고 있는데 널 어떻게 미팅에 내보내?"
그러나 달라진 건 그것을 받아들이는 나의 태도다.
우선 내 복장이 직장생활에 적절하지 않았나 돌아보는 동시에
내가 이 말에 상처받을 이유가 없음을 다시 한번 상기했다.
.
남자다움, 여자다움을 규정짓고 그 틀에 맞지 않는 개인을 배격하는 것은 불합리하다. 이 간단한 이치를 이제 나는 선명히 안다.
.
이것만으로도 나의 일상은 크게 달라졌다.
그 큰 줄기에 서지현 검사의 #metoo 가 있다.
.
서 검사와 같은 이들의 용기와 인내가 조금씩 이 사회를 바꿔나가고
나와 같은 개인이 차별을 대물림하지 않는다면
10년 뒤, 20년 뒤의 사회는 지금보다 나아지겠지.
.
차이가 차별이 되지 않는 세상을 꿈꾼다.
.
세상 모든 종이의 리뷰, 디디.
.
name: 편집자 디디

'' . 그 말을 들었을 때 나는 주위를 둘러봤다 . 작은 실내에 그의 후배들이 자리를 채우고 있었다 . 그때의 나의 기분 , 나의 좌절 , 나의 실망 , 사회자의 표정을 아직도 잊을 수 없다 . 나는 한 마디도 할 수 없었다 . 그날 이후로 나는 서지현 검사에게 부채감을 느낀다 . . 올해의 인물 , 서지현 검사 . 과 선정 . 2018년은 나의 관념이 급변한 해였다 . 나뿐만 아니라 모두가 그럴 것이다 . 대체로 의 피해자였던 내가 가해자 또한 될 수 있다는 강렬한 깨달음을 얻은 것이 가장 큰 수확이다 . 올해는 한국형 권력과 젠더 문제의 혼합이 가져온 혼란 속에 내 의견을 정립하는 것조차 어려웠다 . 이런 혼란이 긍정적인 토론과 합의의 장으로 나아간다면 더없이 좋을텐데 말이다 . . 이런 난리통에 서로 조심하는 분위기가 생겨났다지만 며칠 전에도 나는 여자애답지 못한 복장과 헤어스타일을 상사에게 지적받았다 . `` 여자는 사회 생활할 때 예쁘게 하고 다녀야해 . 넌 여자애가 그게 뭐니 . 그 머리를 하고 있는데 널 어떻게 미팅에 내보내 ? '' 그러나 달라진 건 그것을 받아들이는 나의 태도다 . 우선 내 복장이 직장생활에 적절하지 않았나 돌아보는 동시에 내가 이 말에 상처받을 이유가 없음을 다시 한번 상기했다 . . 남자다움 , 여자다움을 규정짓고 그 틀에 맞지 않는 개인을 배격하는 것은 불합리하다 . 이 간단한 이치를 이제 나는 선명히 안다 . . 이것만으로도 나의 일상은 크게 달라졌다 . 그 큰 줄기에 서지현 검사의 가 있다 . . 서 검사와 같은 이들의 용기와 인내가 조금씩 이 사회를 바꿔나가고 나와 같은 개인이 차별을 대물림하지 않는다면 10년 뒤 , 20년 뒤의 사회는 지금보다 나아지겠지 . . 차이가 차별이 되지 않는 세상을 꿈꾼다 . . 세상 모든 종이의 리뷰 , 디디 . .

text:
retrospectiva 2018:

20/01 scarlett participou da marcha das mulheres em los angeles, organizado pelo movimento "time's up", que luta pela igualdade entre gêneros e contra o assédio. fundado em 1° de janeiro de 2018 o movimento time's up, é composto por mais de 300 mulheres do universo do entretenimento em hollywood, scarlett é uma delas. 💙

scarlett fez um discurso poderoso e inspirador: "avançar significa que minha filha vai crescer em um mundo onde ela não precisa se tornar uma vítima do que se tornou a norma social. a igualdade de gênero não pode existir apenas fora de nós - deve existir dentro também. devemos assumir a responsabilidade não apenas por nossas ações, mas por nós mesmos". 💙

"the best thing a woman can bring to relationship to make her valuable in the eyes of a man who truly wants her is not her ability to help him financially or her ability to be able to take care of herself." this woman is the female derrick jaxn telling lies to women. let's just analyze the first sentence.

a man does not value  a woman that can take care of herself.......false.

most men deal with women who cant take care of themselves financially. if taking care of yourself financially is the primary form of taking care of yourself, you are lost, whether you are a man or a woman.

taking care of yourself includes taking care of your mind, body and spirit. a feminine healthy minded woman is a woman that takes care of herself mebtally and that is rare and attractive. a woman who lives by a higher spiritual code is a woman that takes care of herself spiritually and nothing in a woman is sexier than that.

a woman that comes to the table looking to build will be more desireable than a woman seeking handouts needing a man to take care of her. the average woman in the west is seeing handouts, you have 100,000+ women that have begged men for cashapp and paypal money in the last 25 minutes alone.

proverbs 31:14-22

this woman works and provides for her family. she shops for material to create clothes so her husband doesn't have to spend money on clothes. she saves him money with her hands and brings in money with her hands.

14 she is like the merchant ships,  bringing her food from afar.
15 she gets up while it is still night;  she provides food for her family  and portions for her female servants.
16 she considers a field and buys it;  out of her earnings she plants a vineyard.
17 she sets about her work vigorously;  her arms are strong for her tasks.
18 she sees that her trading is profitable,  and her lamp does not go out at night.
19 in her hand she holds the distaff  and grasps the spindle with her fingers.
20 she opens her arms to the poor  and extends her hands to the needy.
21 when it snows, she has no fear for her household;  for all of them are clothed in scarlet.
22 she makes coverings for her bed;  she is clothed in fine linen and purple.

text:
state lawmakers are looking for ways to strengthen new york’s sexual harassment laws.⁣
⁣
in january, queens assemblywoman aravella simotas and bronx state senator alessandra biaggi will introduce a package of six bills to enhance victims of harassment to seek justice.⁣
⁣
they worked on the legislation with the sexual harassment working group, which consists of seven former legislative staffers who experienced, witnessed or reported sexual harassment. ⁣
⁣
simotas said speaking to the group has given her a broader perspective and better understanding of survivors’ needs.⁣
⁣
“countless high-profile cases of misconduct and the resulting #metoo movement have put a spotlight on the pervasive and persistent problems of sexual harassment,” she said in a statement. “fighting sexual harassment is a complex battle.”

text:
some days i loathe the feeling of her neediness, breastfeeding a toddler is demanding on your body and mind. feeding aversions are real, being touched out is real and feeling resentful of her constant need for my body is real too.

there have been huge personal boundary lessons come up in my experience of breastfeeding. throughout the unpacking and healing of my history of sexual abuse i came to realize that my personal boundaries were totally fucked up from a childhood where my body was not my own. my body was merely a plaything for my abusers and as a result i have never exercised my own bodily autonomy very well.

breastfeeding a toddler has taught me to exercise my “fuck no muscle” (thanks for the term @the_angela_gallo) more than i have ever had the power to in my life, and it’s definitely not always easy, but for helping me find this i am forever grateful to her.

as we approach my personal goal of 2 years i will continue to honour my own new sense of autonomy and boundaries and the feelings of discomfort and sit with them.

breastfeeding is a two-way relationship, and we will stop, when i am done or she is done. whichever comes first.

et pourtant, il peut être source d’optimisme. il existe car une brèche a été ouverte et que les activistes se relaient pour la transformer en révolution. 
en bonus : le best of des newsletters les plus lues en 2018. 🎉🎉🎉

text:
that feeling when you just changed your kid diaper and 1 min later, surprise. 🤦🏽‍♀️ so many emotions and thoughts run through my mind.  #1 really kid 🤦🏽‍♀️
#2 you couldn’t do that in the last diaper🙄
#3 you do know diapers ain’t cheap and we can’t afford to be waisting money like this. ok
#4 then it’s a number two 😩
#5 keep still, why are you running away 😠
#6 f@$k you got doo doo on my hands 🤯🤬
#7 let me calm down you’re just a baby 😌
#8 you better not do it agin 😒

20 mins later, we’re here again huh 🤦🏽‍♀️ #baby #kids #perfectkidz #babychronicles #wednesdaymotivation #theparrenttrapclub #venting #holidays #blog #babyblog #babyblogger #mommy #mommyvent #metoo

text:
i used to be that woman. i made my entire world revolve around the man i was involved with at the time.  it would not be an exaggeration to say that all of the men i ever dated were terrible matches for me. i couldn’t give them what they wanted and they certainly couldn’t give me what i wanted or needed.  i was raised by incredibly strong, resilient women. yet they didn’t know the horrors i suffered and as a result, i became an expert at hiding that pain. i walked a very dark path full of anguish and secret sorrow for many years.  eventually, i destroyed myself. healing was not easy-it was filled with pain and hard work that will continue for the rest of my life. as i laid alone in the rubble that was once my life, tears steaming down my face,  i heard the voices and felt the spirit of all the strong women in my family who had passed before, imploring me, “get up!! get up, get up, get up! this is your truth. own it.  you are stronger than you think. you will survive this. you will heal...and you will rise.” #shewillrise #abusesurvivor #womanwarrior #selflove #selfworth #strengthquotes #powerfulwomen #yougotthis #yougogirl #womanempowerment #youhavesuchaprettyface #gotfaith #survivor #metoo #courage #courageouswomen  #becourageous #trustgod
#workingonme  #thisisme #iamenough #selfcare #selflove #selfesteem #survivor #womanwarrior  #imokay #ptsdawareness #ptsd #ptsdrecovery

text:
in the heart of holiday giving, @thebrittpiper and i are giving one scholarship to someone (maybe you?!) towards our @onthemendretreat in march, for a value of 40% off.
•
we are accepting submissions through 1.4.19. to enter:
👉🏻 visit the “on the mend idyllwild” link in our bio
👉🏻 join seek retreat
👉🏻 press “request booking” to apply for the retreat (no payment needed)
👉🏻 submit your response in the text box, explaining why this healing retreat is so important to you!
•
we will announce the winner on 1.5.19. we can’t wait to get to know you all more, and walk alongside you in this journey!
**those who have already signed up or applied for the retreat are not eligible to apply for this scholarship.**
•
can you envision yourself waking up in a cozy and serene lodge high up in the california mountains, or taking in the sunrise amongst the joshua tree desert? how about unplugging, moving inward, flowing & stretching, breaking bread and forming community over fireside chats and nourishing meals? how about finding peace, forgiveness, acceptance and freeing yourself from past heartache? sounds like a dream right? if you can envision it, we want to support you in making that dream a reality.
•
•
•

text: how about a day after christmas present? ladies and gentlemen...i'd like to introduce you to our 2019 sctc keynote speaker, the incomparable van barnes! in terms of googleability, van is probably best known as the first person to out the cis male lead actor who was eventually fired from amazon’s award winning and critically acclaimed tv show transparent when she joined the #metoo movement, disclosing her experience working several seasons as personal assistant to the lead actor. although her first on-screen credit came in francis ford coppola’s 1983 movie "rumble fish", she can be found on youtube in the 1995 wigstock movie as well as a string of 1990’s daytime talk show appearances, and was a nyc club kid in the early 90’s. she was also featured in two seasons of "i am cait" on the e channel. she transitioned twice before she got it right and today is living her dream married to big daddy living a hetero-normative hillbilly lifestyle keeping chickens in the ozark foothills of missouri and does hair in nearby st. louis. her green acres trans-life is inspirational to many as she offers her brutally honest satirical opinions about her journey. we are so happy to have her with us for our 2019 conference! she's awesome!!! #sctc2019 #greatertogether #vanbarnes

text:
this post is for a friend. everyone's been jumping on the #metoo movement this year. i've kind of kept quiet, because i am very open about the fact that i was sexually assaulted and have been for most my 20s. it's not something to hide in shame over, because i didn't do anything wrong. sometimes i joke about it now, because it diffuses the memory and gives it less power. 
but my friend and i were talking about the kavanagh case. and dude, if i wanted to prove someone raped me when i was 13, i would have no proof. there is literally no proof against kavanagh...or against my rapist. that doesn't mean my rape didn't happen, or that christine ford is a liar. we don't know because there's not enough proof. but what this shows me is to keep talking. because i pray the world my nieces and nephews grow up in will be one where when something happens, you tell someone immediately and the rapist gets in trouble because there's fucking proof. no more shame or hidden family secrets. and men, your voice is in listening, really, hearing what we are saying. because if you do, you'll see us. 
#metoomovement #feminism #rapeculture #jointheclub #slutwalk #circa2014 #maleprivilege #girlpower
name: Sophia Nasreen

text: read on if you’re ready for a rant because i’m so tired of men asking women if they have a boyfriend. first off, it suggests that either a woman has a boyfriend and is off limits to other men only because of that, or she is single and available. (they can’t accept the fact that, say, she’s just not interested or not interested in men, or not looking for a partner). then, if a woman tells a man that yes she does have a boyfriend (whether this is true or a method of avoiding advances) the man will say something like “well where is he then?” i’ve been sent so many comments like this time and time again. stop assuming that women who are alone (on the street in a bar etc) are there for you. #stopstreetharassment

text: just a reminder that i’m the reason why the women’s march imploded. today it was announced that the chicago women’s march has been canceled. if i had not confronted alyssa milano and the rest of the #metoo  panel and asked them to disavow linda sarsour like i did in this video in october, nobody would even be talking about this. sharia = jew hatred. sharia = homophobia. sharia= oppression of women. linda sarsour is an advocate of sharia. the media will never give me credit, but the proof is in the pudding. who else confronted sarsour and milano face to face about sharia?! nobody. i’m the only one. this video went viral and forced them to respond. it has been seen millions of times and got international press coverage. even the left wing media was forced to recognize me. 1.5 weeks later milano disavowed sarsour and the rest of the dominos fell. as you can see in true women’s march fashion, they tried to cover up their jew hatred by silencing me and censoring me by physically removing me. this is what they did to jewish women who were a part of the women’s march. they bullied and silenced them. #exposed #loomered

text:
læs den fulde sammenhængende artikel omkring min tid i #forsvaret og de daglige krænkelser på www.facebook.com/intuitivementor.dk.
.
har aldrig delt denne sårbare historie med dig - men da den lige kom frem i min bevidsthed, vil jeg gerne dele den med dig, den med sergenten der kom ud i badet til vi kvinder, mens vi stod under bruseren, vi kun 18 og 19 år gamle kvinder.
.
september 1995 er jeg 18 år gammel. blandt 5 andre kvinder indtræder jeg i det danske forsvar som værnepligtig soldat (med værneret) og skal aftjene min værnepligt de næste 9 måneder ved kongens artilleriregiment i sjælsmark.
.
1 billede - meget ung, meget naiv, genert og introvert. knapt seksuelt aktiv og samtidig også en lille bulderbasse der havde noget hun skulle bevise. er vokset op på landet (fyn) og er lidt gammeldags og værner derfor om min seksualitet. pornoblade og sexistiske nedladende tale omkring kvinder, det kender jeg ikke rigtig til, indtil nu.
.
jeg søgte ind til det danske forsvar, mhp at blive politibetjent. (hvor jeg blev optaget i år 2000). glædede mig sådan til at blive soldat. lige siden jeg havde været en lille pige ville jeg være politibetjent, hvilket man først kunne søge ind som, når man blev 21 år gammel. så for at samle flere point til at blive politibetjent, tog jeg en uddannelse som salgsassistent i magasin. .
i al den tid jeg var i lære i magasin lyngby, talte jeg ikke om andet "jeg skulle ind og være soldat". jeg både spillede fodbold og boksede, for at komme i god form.

der er lidt tumult på kasernen både den første dag og tiden derefter, for vi pådrager os en del opmærksomhed vi unge kvinder. bl.a. fordi vi fjernes fra hele vores deling og samlet må gå indtrådt ned på depotet og få taget mål til vores sports-bh.

det kunne ikke foregå i fred og ro, nej det blev gjort til noget stort. sports-bh opmålingen blev en form for "udstillings parade" så alle andre kunne se at stabsbatteriet 5 artilleriafdeling stolt kunne fremvise deres første kvinder...
#detdanskeforsvar #soldat #værnepligt #hæren #overkonstabel #konstabel #kvinderiforsvaret #sexisme #kønsdiskrimination #metoo #kvinder #kvindeligsoldat #ligestilling #warrior #metoo #krænkelse #kvindedebat
name: ☆ Love Shaman & Alchemist ☆

text:
i never thought i’d be brave enough to share this part of my life. though this is painful to share, i know we are stronger when we talk about our struggles-and i hope you will share yours with me below. (#metoo)
⠀
when i was 21 i was slipped a date-rape drug.
the remaining details are not significant to my story, but something was taken from me that night that i’ll never get back.
⠀
the final words i was left with were “i only gave you what you deserved”...which were words that pierced my heart and mind for many years to come.
⠀
what i...deserved???
⠀
i immediately turned to food for comfort. honestly, the more weight i gained-the safer i felt. i felt like if i was overweight, no one would find me attractive and i wouldn’t ever get hurt again.
⠀
but the weight that i carried pierced much deeper.
⠀
instead of dealing with it, i tucked it away in my mind and hoped i would never have to face it. i started eating my feelings instead...
⠀
the sad reality is: 1 in 6 women will be a victim of sexual assault/rape. and it’s something we don’t talk about. at least i didn’t for many years. it was a secret i hid from the world because i felt so ashamed.
nobody is deserving of that. nobody. and it took me many years to fully believe that.
⠀
i didn’t take care of myself anymore...
i didn’t love myself anymore...
food was the only comfort that i had...
the thought of taking it away made me uncomforable.
⠀
but i took my life back...and so can you. i share this with you, because i know i’m not alone. many of us had an event that triggered us to gain weight. but the beautiful thing is: you have the power within you to overcome it.
.
.

i never thought i’d be brave enough to share this pa of my life. though this is painful to share, i know we are stronger when we talk about our struggles-and i hope you will share yours with me below. (etoo)
⠀
when i was 21 i was slipped a date-rape drug.
the remaining details are not significan not to my story, but something was taken from me that night that i’ll never get back.
⠀
the final words i was left with were “i only gave you what you deserved”...which were words that pierced my hea and mind for many years to come.
⠀
what i...deserved???
⠀
i immediately turned to food for comfo. honestly, the more weight i gained-the safer i felt. i felt like if i was overweight, no one would find me attractive and i wouldn’t ever get hu again.
⠀
but the weight that i carried pierced much deeper.
⠀
instead of dealing with it, i tucked it away in my mind and hoped i would never have to face it. i staed eating my feelings instead...
⠀
the sad reality is: 1 in 6 women will be a victim of sexual assault/rape. and it’s something we don’t talk about. at least i didn’t for many years. it was a secret i hid from the world because i felt so ashamed.
nobody is deserving of that. nobody. and it took me many years to fully believe that.
⠀
i didn’t take care of myself anymore...
i didn’t love myself anymore...
food was the only comfo that i had...
the thought of taking it away made me uncomforable.
⠀
but i took my life back...and so can you. i share this with you, because i know i’m not alone. many of us had an event that triggered us to gain weight. but the beautiful thing is: you have the power within you to overcome it.
.

text: india and the new confident woman. the eyes may look familiar, as i have featured her daughter in a previous post. yes, follower, this is the mother of the prospective future ‘gypsy queen.’ she is fearless, confident and highly focused and for me, represents the new confident indian woman. this woman and millions of others in india, are saying to men: ‘that’s enough. no more harassment of women.’ those who have been to india and have used the delhi metro, will be aware of the provision of ‘women only’ carriages. those who have used the railways would be familiar with the signs near the train toilets, reminding men, that: ‘harassing women passengers is a punishable offence.’ there is a need for this provision and reminders to men are still required. things are beginning to improve, but there is a long way to go. finally, just a reminder to men of what constitutes ‘harassment of women,’ under the indian penal code and the railways act: obscene remarks, teasing, touching, stares, gestures, songs and unwanted attention are all forms of sexual violence, punishable by up to 2 years! 2019 should be the ‘empowerment of women year’ #india #indian #indiaphotostory #india_everyday #indianwoman #womenpowerment #metoo #metoomovement #metooindia #metoo❤️ #travelstory #indiaphotostory #indiadiaries #indiatraveldiaries #worldtravelpics #travelphotographer #travelphoto #storyteller #storytellers #streetphoto #streetphotocolour #faces #worldfaces #worldstreetphotography #travelstories #travelstoriesworld

text:
the omen days of christmas have begun!  this celtic tradition helps you find themes to empower each month of the coming year.  starting today, dec 26, each of the next 12 days represents a month of the year, 2019,  so today applies to january. look for something that seems to have meaning for you, and that is your january theme. over the 12 days, you do this for each month. 
traditionally, these omens were found in nature, perhaps by taking a walk to identify something that has significance for you, and noting that this is a message for that month.  in my personal practice, i don’t limit the omen search to nature, but choose something that speaks to me that day.  often it is in my family or personal life, or even from something sparked by a fb post.  this morning, for example, i am attracted to a video retrospective on the building of women’s inner fire for change in 2018, starting with the #metoo movement.  i may use this as my january omen, and stay alert to ideas for personal action during the month. 
last year was my first year doing this, and i loved the process.  i wrote a few words about each month in 2018, and referred to them throughout the year, especially on the first day of the month. it was fun to see these as themes and build an action intention around them.  there is no wrong way to do this, so whatever works for you is fine.  what i like most about the omen days is that the meaning comes entirely from what seems important to me. last year, my intentions were about my personal life, but this year i think i am going to expand my themes to include some culture changing goals. i am doing this again, starting today.  who else is doing it with me?  feel free to tag me in posts, post in this thread, or post over on my karen crane, lifestyle alchemy page.  let’s have some fun!  #wisdomwork  #lifestylealchemy

last year was my first year doing this, and i loved the process.  i wrote a few words about each month in 2018, and referred to them throughout the year, especially on the first day of the month. it was fun to see these as themes and build an action intention around them.  there is no wrong way to do this, so whatever works for you is fine.  what i like most about the omen days is that the meaning comes entirely from what seems impoant to me. last year, my intentions were about my personal life, but this year i think i am going to expand my themes to include some culture changing goals. i am doing this again, staing today.  who else is doing it with me?  feel free to tag me in posts, post in this thread, or post over on my karen crane, lifestyle alchemy page.  let’s have some fun!

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
what if anxious really was anticipatory?
what if fear were really the guidepost of where to go?
what if the nervous energy behind putting off that one conversation you need to have is really your guardian angels saying, “do it!”
what if the sweet almost indulgent feel of doing something solely for you was a universal nod in the direction you should do?

when i had a strict meal plan i used the energy of cravings to do something: yoga, dance, writing, hiking. 
when i was getting sober i used the energy of cravings and irritation to notice things around me i had ignored for years. 
maybe, the flutter that we may call nerves or anxiety is really just energy saying, “yes”

fill your own cup first so we can teach all generations how’s it’s done.  because when one woman heals, she also heals her mother, her daughter and all the women around her. 
so.  much.  love.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
it's the festive season and it's supposed to  be a happy season for all, but my mood went dark immediately i saw this.
.
according to reports, she was 300 level university student and showed no signs or depression prior.
.
she took a poison to end her life but not before living a note, bidding her loved ones farewell.
.
depression is *not* a myth. it is real. it kills it's victim slowly, constantly pushing limits. .
please if you suspect depression in you or someone you know, report and seek help as soon as possible. you will be saving a life. .
if you do not know how to get help directly, send us a message on here and we'll walk the walk with you; but the first step is always breaking silence.
. 
you are not alone!!!
.

🗒hеllo: каким вы были ребенком? что помните с тех времен?
📌 джан: я родился и вырос в районе суадие на улице багдад. был единственным ребенком и всегда имел любящую семью. сначала я учился в колледже бильен, затем в итальянском вузе. 
мои студенеские годы прошли между обучением и баскетбольными тренировками. вставал в  5:30 утра и шел в школу, после школы шел домой, а в 19:30 ходил на тренироки в tеkеlspor . tekelspor в то время был в первой баскетбольной лиге. тренироки были продолжительными, так что домой я зачастую возвращался  уже заполночь. на следющий день был тот же темп.

📌 джан: я родился и вырос в районе суадие на улице багдад. был единственным ребенком и всегда имел любящую семью. сначала я учился в колледже бильен, затем в итальянском вузе. 
мои студенеские годы прошли между обучением и баскетбольными тренировками. вставал в  5:30 утра и шел в школу, после школы шел домой, а в 19:30 ходил на тренироки в tеkеlspor . tekelspor в то время был в первой баскетбольной лиге. тренироки были продолжительными, так что домой я зачастую возвращался  уже заполночь. на следющий день был тот же темп.

text:
ever find it difficult to choose?  to be present with your kids vs working your business?  yep - #metoo
.
what i’ve realized as a #wahm to keep from feeling the full weight of #momguilt is that i need to surround myself with other work at home moms.  our kids may play more video games, and eat grilled cheese or take out more nights out of the week than other kids but they are also seeing creativity, resiliency and the will to work for more!
.
thankful for my #socialmedia groups of wahms and other boss business women who have decided to support me in the truth that my decision to work from home isn’t about choosing something over them, it was a decision about choosing them!
.

or when i was at a theater and a man sat beside me. while the theater he whispered dirty things in my ears, i couldn’t believe what he said to me. so i said “what the hell are you saying to me?!” and he starting to say “hora” “bitch” “fitta” “dra åt helvete”. i got scared i walked away. 
or...
i was walking home alone. a man followed me. he was so scary, dark, hands in the pocket. i started to run but he just starting to run after me. when i was almost home he took his hand on me and i got scared. then i screamed “stop, if tou dont stop following me i will call the police” and he walked away. i got home told what just happened and yeah. 
so... i know the feelings. don’t feel alone. i just wanted to say, we all are in danger but we all can save it. bye! love ya all☺️💕 #metoo #noisano #stopwiththisshit

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

text:
(ulasan yang dibuat oleh om nurkholis sastro, @cahayaperempuanwcc )
——————————-
“membongkar budaya patriarki” dengan komunikasi budaya (film). minggu siang kemarin, matahari terasa menyengat setelah hujan gerimis di sidorejo dan banyumans. petang itu kami nonton dan diskusi film perawan, elina, dan aedin.

dalam proses nonton, banyak ibu-ibu yang komentar dengan bisik-bisik kepada teman di sebelahnya.

dengan hati-hati lica veronika menyampaikan secara runtut pesan yang ada di film-film tersebut berdasarkan pemikiran sutradaranya.

saya tahu bapak-bapak dan ibu-ibu yang hadir tersentuh oleh film-film tersebut. tapi mereka agak malu  berkomentar panjang soal film ketika diskusi. “kita ingin menyelesaikan masalah perkawinan anak, kehamilan tidak diinginkan, dan relasi gender di dunia remaja. kadang kita bisa melewati persoalan sendiri. tapi terkadang butuh kehadiran keluarga dan para tetangga”.
———————————terima kasih sudah mau berproses bersama ❤️
yang terbaik @ritafransiscadwi @cahayaperempuanwcc

text:
did you know that a rabbit’s spine is extremely fragile? in contrast, its hind leg muscles are very strong, hence their reputation for jumping high and running fast, particularly from predators. however, when a rabbit is caught in the grips of a predator, the rabbit’s legs are strong enough to break its own spine if it struggles to break free. 
these scarves are printed with the imagery of a rabbit’s spine, hybridized with knuckledusters, creating an armor for the once fragile spine. these scarves will be for sale soon on my etsy. @lawless_forest .

text:
“tóxico" é a palavra do ano eleita pelo dicionário oxford
a instituição explicou o motivo da escolha dessa palavra em seu site: “a palavra do ano da oxford é uma palavra ou expressão que é julgada como um reflexo do ethos, do humor ou das preocupações do ano que está chegando ao fim. ela tem um potencial duradouro como termo de significado cultural".
a oxford apontou um aumento de 45% no número de vezes que os usuários pesquisaram a palavra no ano de 2018 e relata que depois de “química”, a palavra que frequentemente a acompanha é “masculinidade”. o termo masculinidade tóxica se refere à epidemia de direitos masculinos, alienação e violência que deram origem ao movimento #metoo cuja a luta é contra o assédio e agressão sexual.
fonte: https://revistagalileu.globo.com/ #oxford #palavradoano #2018 #liapinheiro

text:
happy holidays butterflies. 🦋🦋🦋
.
.
i was asked a lot about the big “t” word this week: trust! .
.i heard again and again- can i recover confidence in myself making good life decisions? can i trust people again and stop feeling guilty after having said #metoo? or when i am smiling on the outside but aching on the inside..
.yes, you can with 1 simple tool, that we go more deeply into in my masterclass. bottom line inventory.
..here are simple steps to create yours:.
.take out a sheet of paper right now and write down all the things that you cannot stand. the things that piss you off. 📝 give yourself 5 minutes to just go to town… ..now trust, without judgement or letting that negative self talk creep on in… write down 2 words next to each one. write down- 1) handle it. 2) cannot handle it..
.take a moment and be with your list. now send trust to that list. trust that you can and deserve to honor your bottom line. and see what it feels like to be with the handle it vs. not handle it side. ..see you in the next post! i hope you can have your list by then! .
.
. [photo credit: friends & family photo shot at recent holiday gathering: dress like a celebrity theme. mandara left, sacred right] #bottomlineinventory #kuumbahealth #resilience #metoo #stresscontrol #stressmastery #trust

text:
#suhelseth gets married to model girlfriend, #lakshmimenon, amidst sexual harassment rumours.

reports about #suhel #seth getting engaged to his model girlfriend, #lakshmi #menon, started doing the rounds right when he was accused of #sexual #harassment by multiple women from the industry. the two reportedly got engaged at his apartment in #gurugram and headed to #goa and #switzerland for a romantic post-engagement #vacation. the two have now tied the knot in a private ceremony at his apartment in gurugram, as per reports in #mumbai mirror. the two got married yesterday and a source told the daily, “it was a quiet, genteel affair, and the guests were people who are close to suhel and who he counts as friends.” the guests included #prafulpatel, #jaypanda, #amarsingh, #muzaffarali, #tasneem, tarun tejpal, #sheiladixit and a couple of other close friends. well, looks like congratulations are in order for the writer-columnist despite all the #sexualharassment accusations against him. the two haven’t confirmed it on social #media yet or to any other portal, for that matter. while we are eagerly hoping to see an official announcement soon, we wish the #newlyweds #hearty #congratulations for their new life ahead. this has definitely come as a shock to many that the two are now married.

#metoo #metoomovement #aaiwa #news

text:
the not-so-great-moments...
.
.
i’m not one to do covers but this song inspired me a long time ago about what real songwriting is all about.  james taylor wrote “fire and rain” about a child hood friend that committed suicide, his battle with drug addiction, and his experience being in a mental hospital 😳. you can’t get more realer than that 💯. that’s songwriting to me...the ability and courage to show all of you. ✍🏾
.
.
whatever our passions are via art, work, relationships, or just life...we shouldn’t be afraid of showing all of us...including all our vices, our struggles, our pain, the good, the bad, and even the not-so-great moments of our life.  being vulnerable and open shouldn’t make you feel embarrassed and it doesn’t make you weak...it makes you inspiring.💜✨💫 #imabeautifulmess
.
.
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

.

text: a lot of you may know i have been very open about my body over the years, but i’m here to say that it has not always been like that. in the age of social media it is hard to love yourself everyday, and yes i still get anxiety some days. you cannot always be at your best, but as long as we respect each other and learn to treat everyone equally, that depression and anxiety can disappear. this year has taught me a lot about loving myself and just embracing what it means to be a woman in 2018, and let me say this, i’m so damn proud. i’m going to keep sending love and positive vibes through my feed in the way i choose to. also if it isn’t known already, this photo doesn’t represent sex and is definitely not an invitation asking for it, stop sexualizing nudity. as well, if you don’t like my feed you can get the fuck off of it then, unfollow ya girl! 🤷🏼‍♀️ #loveyourself

“robert, you don’t get to tell my story.”—andrea kelly, r.kelly’s ex-wife /// lifetime released the first trailers for the docu-series on r.kelly titled, ‘surviving r. kelly’. the series will be aired over six episodes and feature interviews with kelly’s ex-wife andrea kelly and other victims including, jerhonda pace, lisa van allen, asante mcgee, kitti jones, and more. john legend and wendy williams are also slated to appear. “you don’t get to tell people that we got divorced because i had a problem with being a stay-at-home mom. we got divorced because i was no longer going to sit and be violated. what he did to me was criminal.”— andrea kelly /// share this story.-

📣#ywrnewyork speaker announcement! 📣 jazmin kay @jazminlkay is executive director of 18by.vote @18by.vote, a non-profit organization which aims to help young people understand how, when, and why to vote. jazmin was named as one of @hercampus her campus’ “22 under 22 most inspiring college women” and has appeared on the @todayshow and @goodmorningamerica. she is the former voting rights and civic engagement reporter at generation progress at the center for american progress @americanprogress. jazmin has interned in government offices on many levels including the white house under president @barackobama, where she was the youngest white house intern, the office of senator @kirstengillibrand (d-ny), and the office of the ulster county executive in upstate new york. 
jazmin's writing has been seen in @seventeen, @mtv, @teenvogue, @huffpost, @rookiemag, @nationmag, the white house blog, u.s. department of state blog and more. she is currently a student at @gwuniversity, dc studying political science. 📣 get tickets to see jazmin speak at young women run new york!  link in bio 📣
.
.
.

text:
the bravest and most difficult thing you can ever do is be who you were created to be. 
you don’t just wake up one morning and say, “this is who i am and i love me.” if only it were that simple. 
losing 243 pounds didn’t make me love myself, in fact, i didn’t even like myself. baring my soul, owning my truth, and slaying the shame that controlled me my entire life— that was the beginning of the best love story of my life.....developing a positive relationship with myself..... that is where the magic was hidden all along. ❤️👑 #shewillrise #abusesurvivor #womanwarrior #beforeandafterweightloss #selfworth #strengthquotes #powerfulwomen #yougotthis #yougogirl #womanempowerment #youhavesuchaprettyface #gotfaith #survivor #metoo #courage #courageouswomen  #becourageous #trustgod
