text:
tóxico} (retirado do site da revista galileu)

em 2015, a palavra do ano era “fofo”. três anos depois, o dicionário oxford elegeu uma palavra não tão positiva assim: 2018 é o ano do “tóxico”. a instituição explicou o motivo da escolha dessa palavra em seu site: “a palavra do ano da oxford é uma palavra ou expressão que é julgada como um reflexo do ethos, do humor ou das preocupações do ano que está chegando ao fim. ela tem um potencial duradouro como termo de significado cultural". a oxford apontou um aumento de 45% no número de vezes que os usuários pesquisaram a palavra no ano de 2018 e relata que depois de “química”, a palavra que frequentemente a acompanha é “masculinidade”. o termo masculinidade tóxica se refere à epidemia de direitos masculinos, alienação e violência que deram origem ao movimento #metoo cuja a luta é contra o assédio e agressão sexual.

e aí, pra você também foi esta a palavra do ano?

text:
принимай реальность и меняй будущее!
знаешь, я ведь, как и ты, не особо «в масле катаюсь»! наши проблемы и трудности во многом схожи.
но я не согласна с ними мириться!
знаешь, в какой-то момент я сказала себе: «хватит!
надо что-то менять! надо что-то делать!» я осознала, что меня не устраивает то, как я живу! 
я поняла, что хочу быть финансово свободной! хочу иметь собственную квартиру!
машину!
я хочу по-настоящему помочь своим детям! быть сильной, уважаемой личностью! реализовать свой потенциал!
наконец, я хочу увидеть мир!!!! когда я это осознала - я начала искать возможность и нашла ее! теперь это не только моя возможность - но и твоя! 
давай вместе менять нашу жизнь, ведь если мы этого не сделаем, то возможно, все останется как есть, навсегда! давай вместе, прямо сейчас, начнем делать то, что поможет нам вырваться из нашего замкнутого круга, пока он окончательно не задушил в нас наши желания и мечты!

text:
i had a weird epiphany today. it was something like, in order to feel safe in the general area i have to believe they weren’t all bad.

maybe only like, 78% bad or 82% bad. i thought about 63% bad for a while but that seemed too big a lie to sell to myself. i have them up as about 3500% bad at present so we’re already talking quite a large reduction.

i should qualify “bad”. bad is a lot of things, like it turns out a feeling that’s “bad” is a lot of different feelings. so “bad” in this case is short for all of the forces of self-interest, lack of awareness, abuse of power, rigid thinking, absence of empathy, hypocrisy, privilege and so on.

it turns out “bad” in this case is pretty broad so i’m abbreviating it to bad.

then there’s parameters on “them” and they are utterly exclusive of anyone directly involved. it’s a more collective, ultimately faceless entity, this “them”. it has faces though of course, i could guess at some of them. i have guessed at some of them, but this guess work serves no value because i had to deal with a faceless them ultimately and it was not equivalent to the sum of its individual parts.

i have to believe that there was a point where further harm could have been caused but a decision was made not to. i have been attributing this to a lack of realisation on their part but maybe not.

it came to me after my inbox on twitter was once again full of stories from other autistic people in various types of litigation.

they all have their own collective faceless entities on the other side, and when there are opportunities to prolong or increase the harm done in a situation those faceless entities take these.

for the sake of the people who reached out to me i can’t list the examples.

it changes perspective, when i look at my faceless them and consider what it could have done.

that’s not any kind of pass mind you, the bar is literally on the floor after all. just because someone like me came along and forced them to shove a small wedge underneath it doesn’t mean we’re done here, progress achieved, next issue please.

i think i’ll settle on 82% bad, handing out acknowledgment for what should be a minimum standard is still a bit off.

text:
why do i continue to let you hurt me?
why don’t i trust myself to know that i am strong?
i am worth more. 
is it because i am scared to lose the only person that understood me? 
scared to lose the only person that never judged me? although, it has gotten to a point where if i show one positive emotion i am judged for thinking for myself and not needing you to think for me. 
i sometimes put my foot down to regain respect from you, yet it fails. 
i try...
yet i know it’s not for me anymore. 
i am not meant to love you. 
you are not meant to love me. 
we are not meant to love each other. 
i have to learn to let go, which is hard. 
you were all i knew. 
all i dreamt of.
all i wanted. 
i just didn’t get that in return. 
you hurt me. 
i cried. 
i prayed, yet it wasn’t enough. 
it’s time to let go. 
i need to let go. 
i will let go. -carolynn m

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
this afternoon i took some time out for myself, allowed myself to be fully present and grounded. i am always drawn to water this is where i feel most at peace. watching the water cascade over the waterfall is so calming. self care is extremely important , more so when you are going through some challenging times, there is nothing selfish about it. i am so very blessed and grateful to be surrounded by some amazing people that walk alongside me, it is important to keep your tribe close, and let them help when you need it (still learning to do this) one step, one breath, one day at a time, thats all you can do.
❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🦋🌈👣🚗🧘‍♀️🦄🏞️✍️🏥

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
reminder! 👇🏼
.
most people give up their power by believing they don’t have any.
.
focus on the choices you can make to regain your power and pay attention to situations that make you feel powerless. are you willfully giving up your power? are you making sacrifices that cost you peace? are you surrounding yourself with people who lift you up?
.
you are enough. you matter. you are stronger than this. you are made of the universe.
.

text:
s e l f - c a r e // bucket list #advocate #idaho——————————————————————
survivors dealing with or healing from domestic abuse should think about self-care as a vital step in their healing process. having lived through the trauma of an abusive partner, you probably rarely get to feel cared for or made a priority. your most likely put your own needs on the back burner to take care of the things your abuser demanded of you. you may have been made to feel like doing things you enjoyed was selfish. 
it’s time to change that mindset, and the start of the new year can be a good spot to start over. 
survivors, advocates, and support persons were asked, what do you do to practice self-care. we’ve gathered some ideas, which are incorporated on the following list of ways to show yourself some love. —————————————————————— #lifestyle #family #loveshouldnthurt #december #enddv #byui #dvfacts #dancing #entrepreneur #fall #design #wellness #marketing #friends #idaho #timesup #metoo #idaho #health #breakthesilence #idaho #graphicdesign #healthy #winter #christmas

text:
between stimulus and response there is a space. in that space is our power to choose our response. in our response lies our growth and our freedom. ~viktor e. frankl
. . . . .

my thoughts @viptravelgirl

i’ve been thinking about this “space” that viktor e. frankl refers to a lot these past few weeks. mostly because we seem to be in what i like to call a “social (re)awakening” on some many fronts; which has sparked new and also reignited old conversations on so many critical topics like the #metoo movement, #lgbt rights, #civialrights  and so much more.  i only mention these as examples because they are conversations fueled by passionate thoughts and options from many varied perspectives which further validate the meaning of this quote. i’ve always valued my ability to acknowledge this space and use it to see beyond just myself. but i have discovered that this space can and has become somewhat of a burden i’ve come to bare. why? because growing up as a bi-racial girl in conservative america…i’ve always felt obligated to work within the confines of this space. having control over my thoughts, feelings and actions were the best ways to navigate the narrow straights of society. but as i’ve been working through a very emotionally challenging year…i’ve discovered that this space has become nothing more then a catch-all…a space for packaging up all the bullshit perspectives, ignorant ideologies and small-minded thoughts that i’ve been forced to maneuver around over the years. rather then my “space” being a place of growth and freedom…it’s resembled something more closely to a glass box.

the takeaway:
while i will always seek first to understand and then to be understood. it’s time for me to shatter my own glass ceiling in order to make room for myself.  it’s time for me to get comfortable with letting others be uncomfortable. it’s not my job to make me or my awesomeness more palpable for others to swallow. because at the end of the day…if we are all honor our own spaces, we’ll all be better off for it.
name: Meg Sytnick - Travel Expert

while i will always seek first to understand and then to be understood. it’s time for me to shatter my own glass ceiling in order to make room for myself.  it’s time for me to get comfoable with letting others be uncomfoable. it’s not my job to make me or my awesomeness more palpable for others to swallow. because at the end of the day…if we are all honor our own spaces, we’ll all be better off for it.

text: thrilled and proud to share this @ms_magazine article that #kohinurkhyumtithila wrote on @thewitchhuntshow. we are creating a space for diverse women to be heard and to heal - and to laugh along the way. i have been honored to witness so many brave witches sharing their truths and their talents over this past year. many thanks to @cszla for giving us a residency to develop the show and to all the funny, talented and courageous women (and a couple gents as well!) who have shared the stage. it has been an honor. special shout out to #gloriaiseli for helping bring this show to the next level and to ally wizard and good man human @michaeljsielaff who made the call that got the ball rolling and has been a supportive ally and diligent social media maven from the get go. and a witchin’ big thank you to everyone who has come and put your tushies in the seats - we so appreciate your support as we have been discovering this show. excited for what’s to come, witches!! #witchplease #witchcrushwednesday #funnywomen #feminist #diverse #diversestories #theatreoftheabsurd #witchhunt #metoo #timesup #believeher #comedy #varietyshow #lathtr #witch #witchin #jointhecoven

text: sian brown ma ‘20 spoke about a powerful dress designed by rachel powell ‘17: “a key piece in our exhibit, the white dress - 030113, was designed by alumna rachel powell ‘17. the white dress - 030113 represents part of powell’s story, which she has described as a loss of innocence. the numbers 030113 on the bodice of the dress represent the date that she was raped. domestic violence, rape, and sexual assault are subjects that are often unspoken and overlooked in american society; however, in women empowered, these important topics have not been ignored. women unjustly face a great deal of pressure to conform to standards in order to feel safe and equal in a world that has been dominated by their counterparts throughout history. months ahead of all of the recent press and the alarming number of stories coming forth about sexual assault and rape with the #metoo movement, powell displayed this dress in the 2017 @cornellfashionshioncollective runway show. i personally would like to commend ms. rachel powell for the strength to be able to tell her story through clothing, and by doing so, empowering others.” #frontlinefashions #feministfashion #cornellfashion #ccabiennial2018

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

عشق ورزیدنمان و زیستن به عنوان بخشی از یک جامعه انسانی فریادی از تغییر و پیشروی است، تغییر به سمت برابری و آزادی.
وقت آن رسیده که به این تبعیض‌ها پایان دهیم، اولین قدم هم آگاهی و دوری از پیش‌داوری است.
عشق، رهایی است، نه بردگی 🌈
کانال تلگرامی ما 👇

text:
« ce n’est pas la première fois que deuxième page te parle de l’excellente série animée créée par raphael bob-waksberg. les (més)aventures de bojack horseman (will arnett), cheval anthropomorphique et antihéros, s’intensifient dans cette dernière saison, sur fond d’actualité. bojack est un acteur hollywoodien qui a fait sa fortune dans les années 1980 en tant que protagoniste de la sitcom horsin’ around. quand on le découvre, il passe ses journées à se remémorer ses jours de gloire, et à se lamenter sur son sort. depuis la saison 1, il a tenté plusieurs come-back plus ou moins réussis et a déçu plus d’un-e proche avec son attitude égocentrée et erratique. dans la saison 5, il est de toutes les addictions, mais aussi de tous les combats, se réclamant subitement du féminisme. la vie de bojack est un miroir distordu de l’actualité hollywoodienne, et c’est donc sans grande surprise que l’on assiste à l’arrivée du mouvement #metoo dans la fiction. la saison, tout en nuances, inspecte le féminisme dans toute sa complexité, et notamment sa présence dans le show-business. diane nguyen (alison brie), la meilleure amie de bojack veut aider le mouvement en tant que femme journaliste alors que beaucoup de médias ne font que surfer sur la vague. le public s’interroge : est-il possible d’aller jusqu’au bout de cette posture sans devenir hypocrite ? la place des hommes (et leur bonne foi) au sein des mouvements féministes est mise à mal, mais aussi celle des femmes de pouvoir. cette saison est passionnante, savamment dosée en humour noir et en commentaire social. » #bestof
📺 http://bit.ly/topseries2018

text:
« ce n’est pas la première fois que deuxième page te parle de l’excellente série animée créée par raphael bob-waksberg. les (més)aventures de bojack horseman (will arnett), cheval anthropomorphique et antihéros, s’intensifient dans cette dernière saison, sur fond d’actualité. bojack est un acteur hollywoodien qui a fait sa fortune dans les années 1980 en tant que protagoniste de la sitcom horsin’ around. quand on le découvre, il passe ses journées à se remémorer ses jours de gloire, et à se lamenter sur son sort. depuis la saison 1, il a tenté plusieurs come-back plus ou moins réussis et a déçu plus d’un-e proche avec son attitude égocentrée et erratique. dans la saison 5, il est de toutes les addictions, mais aussi de tous les combats, se réclamant subitement du féminisme. la vie de bojack est un miroir distordu de l’actualité hollywoodienne, et c’est donc sans grande surprise que l’on assiste à l’arrivée du mouvement #metoo dans la fiction. la saison, tout en nuances, inspecte le féminisme dans toute sa complexité, et notamment sa présence dans le show-business. diane nguyen (alison brie), la meilleure amie de bojack veut aider le mouvement en tant que femme journaliste alors que beaucoup de médias ne font que surfer sur la vague. le public s’interroge : est-il possible d’aller jusqu’au bout de cette posture sans devenir hypocrite ? la place des hommes (et leur bonne foi) au sein des mouvements féministes est mise à mal, mais aussi celle des femmes de pouvoir. cette saison est passionnante, savamment dosée en humour noir et en commentaire social. » #bestof

text:
у кого чего болит.🎅🏼🍾👱🏼‍♀️👦🏻
⠀
американских детей призывают не  садиться  на колени  к санте, а российским - запретят пить детское шампанское.
⠀
маразм крепчал... больные взрослые, которым нечем заняться везде ищут домогательства и алкоголизм😅
⠀
журналист the washington post описала ситуацию, когда двухлетняя девочка плакала и отказывалась сидеть на коленях сказочного персонажа в торговом центре, а ее мама пыталась сделать традиционную фотографию. журналистка размышляет, какое влияние оказывает на девочек сидение на коленях взрослого мужчины.
⠀
автор признается, что разные родители по-разному отвечают на эти вопросы.
⠀
журналистка отмечает, что для американских детей фотография на коленях у санта-клауса является своеобразным обрядом посвящения, невинным праздничным ритуалом, однако не все родители едины в этом мнении. для некоторых родителей, заявляет шмидт, попытка рассматривать санта-клауса в свете #metoo является политизированием праздника
⠀
по мнению психолога, уроки о согласии и нежелательном прикосновении должны начинаться рано, и родители могут использовать праздничную традицию как возможность научить детей тому, что они контролируют свое тело.репортер добавила, что во время праздничных фотосессий большинство санта-клаусов учат, чтобы их руки всегда были видны.
⠀
а  дедушка мороз на колени никого не сажает 🤔 зато водочки  может хряпнуть😂
⠀
у нас дела обстоят не менее странно )
⠀
«после „детского шампанского“, дети будут курить „детские сигареты“. давайте тогда сделаем „детское вино“!»
⠀
блогеры стебутся - "лучше запретить детский боярышник"
⠀
"никакого детского шампанского. что такое детское шампанское? даже если это просто газированная вода, но она имитирует сам процесс питья, это безобразие, мы приучаем ребёнка.
⠀
— геннадий онищенко"
⠀
я немного в шоке, у меня все. что думаете , может и сам новый год запретить 🤔?
⠀

text:
imelda cortez, a 20-year-old woman in el salvador, who was jailed with attempted murder after she gave birth to her rapist’s baby in a toilet has been freed. cortez was rushed to the hospital in april 2017 after she gave birth to a baby girl fathered by her stepfather, who has raped and sexually abused her since she was 12, in the toilet. cortez said she did not know she was pregnant, but the doctor at the hospital suspected she had tried to abort the baby and called the authorities. cortez was then arrested and handed a 20 year jail sentence after prosecutors argued that failing to tell anyone about her pregnancy or seek medical attention for the baby amounted to attempted murder under the country’s laws, which completely ban abortions. however, on monday, a court ruled that cortez had not tried to kill her child and that she was free to go home. the judge concluded that the court could not have expected her to act differently given the emotional and psychological damage inflicted by the sexual violence she had suffered since childhood. cortez was greeted by family members and supporters outside the courtroom. (📷: getty, reuters)

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i mestieri del cinema sono tanti: un mondo sommerso dietro le quinte, un lavoro silenzioso e costante svolto da una nutrita minoranza di professioniste, creativa, competente e soprattutto combattente in un settore ancora prerogativa degli uomini. anche loro sono state parte del movimento #metoo , perché anche loro, dietro la macchina da presa, hanno subito abusi e le violenze. che ruolo hanno, quindi, le donne nell’universo della produzione video, in italia e all'estero?
ne ho parlato con marta corradi, federica belletti e marisa vallone.
su letteradonna.it

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
i don't think that i can articulate my why better than this! @evancarmichael is absolutely 110% on point!..................................... "i think the why in what you do comes from pain. and i think people are good people in general. like i think humans are good and i'm on team human.
and when you have gone through something painful, you just naturally want to make it easier for the other people who are suffering that same thing.
and i think that human nature is to try and avoid the pain and forget the pain, put it behind us. never go back there, it's a terrible place.
when i think if you actually want to help people you need to run back into your pain. understand what that meant to you and how bad it was and then whatever you did to get over it, then helping other people. make the road a little bit easier"

text:
i've seen this tweet circulate around a lot of feminist pages on here. apparently if two people's lives aren't ruined by a crime, the crime isn't a problem. gun violence isn't a problem because at least 2 people have been shot and lived through it. rape isn't a problem because at least 2 people have led successful lives after being raped. obviously the feminists who use this logic don't apply it universally to all similar situations, just the ones where it benefits the feminist narrative. it's such a laughable and stupid claim to make that false accusations aren't harmful because two people's lives weren't ruined (even though their lives and reputation were definitely damaged), not to mention completely dismissive and ignorant of the men who have had their lives ruined due to false accusations. people have lost jobs and school places over false accusations. people have even lost their lives to them but apparently those people's lives weren't ruined because that didn't happen to these two cherry picked men.
---

text:
los top 5 que marcaron la moda este año.
/
2018 ha sido un año bastante controversial, inició con toda la potencia del movimiento #metoo que había partido el año pasado. despedidas, nuevas tendencias, adquisiciones de marcas y quiebras fueron los tópicos que predominaron este movido año en la industria de la moda.
/
✨partiendo con carolina herrera, quien tuvo su último show antes de despedirse como directora creativa, marcando el fin de una era, siendo wes gordon su sucesor.
/
✨”realmente no me importa, ¿a ti?", era el slogan de la chaqueta verde militar zara que, la primera dama de estados unidos, melania trump, usó en su visita a los niños separados de sus padres en el borde de texas.
/
✨versace es comprado por $2.1 billones de dólares, siendo adquirido por el holding michael kors, que luego pasaria a ser capri holdings. aún así, la icónica donatella versace, dejó claro que seguiría como directora creativa de la marca.
/
✨virgil abloh, el primer hombre de color en ser director creativo de la marca louis vuitton, sucediendo a kim jones, marcando su debut en junio con su primera colección para la marca.
/
✨por una industria libre de piel animal, gucci, michael kors, versace, coach y burberry son algunas de las marcas que apuestan por colecciones libres de materia prima animal.

text:
instagram випустив огляд тенденцій платформи за 2018 рік: цікаво дізнатись чим жила спільнота соціальної мережі в році, що минає? тоді читайтe далі👉
⠀
😍найпопулярнішим стікером в stories став heart love від arata.
💓у стрічці емодзі «серце» зустрічалося в коментарях більше 14 мільярдів разів.
😎найщасливішим місцем на землі визнаний disneyland в токіо.
📲що стосується інтересів аудиторії, то в цьому році продовжували зростати в популярності фото і відео, які викликають приємні до мурашок відчуття (asmr): наприклад, різка мила.😬

text:
to the ones who picked me before i was ripe enough;
the universe bears witness of all injustice,
witness in the form of the air that carries the secrets and cries i'd utter when i'd feel alone on nights filled with darkness of the past,
in the form of the fire that'd rage in my head and heart when i'd think of what life could've been otherwise,
in the form of tears that cleansed my face while i'd attempt to cleanse my body, as if water would wash off marks of your touch,
and in the form of the ground that i'd kneel to and prostrate, until i'd feel pure again,
the universe bears witness and the universe awaits.
#universe #black #tears #head #heart #fire #water #ground #air #ripe #metoo #body #pure #marks #darkness #timesup #secrets #cries #cleanse #rage #poetry #poem

i rewrote this for the women who have been through the storm and rain about beauty. vanity has swept through and told us that we should conform to a falsfied man's image that would never be satisfied. truth be told many women seek approval from those who are not complete themselves because of their own insecurities. i desire to be with a husband who can appreciate beauty not just from the outside, but can build on the inside by uplifting her as a priceless treasure. on my own walk with god, i asked if this was possible because of all the calamities and abuses that i suffer from counterfeits attracted to manipulation and control. i discovered that this is possible living bicariously through other couple's lives who weathered scrutiny, lust, and financial devastation. what is the storm you are willing to endure to protect your own relationship in god's eyesight? i know what i'm graced for and not graced for with boundaries and limitations in which others say, whoaaa! i listen to the politically and poetically correct individuals who spew vomit because will it work in my situation?? only heaven knows.......i will tell my issues to god who created me and can handle the burdens that i can share with everyone. #metoo 
i'm beautiful even with the scars and my hair nappy looking because it's my style that my culture can accept and heritage. look at my brown skin, its rich with education and intellectual sense that i follow and my mind is unrentlenting in grasping and then demonstrating with the manifestation of greatness and wealthy for your company as well as my family. @flowing

text:
świeże, dobre wieści z gruzji. 
w kwietniu 2016 tatia samkharadze zwolniła się z telewizji imedi, ponieważ była molestowana seksualnie przez swojego szefa i bardzo popularnego shalva ramishvili.

w zamian za usługi seksulane prowadzący programu proponował jej karierę w telewizji.

w gruzji, jak wzszędzie, nie jest łatwo udowodnić komuś molestowanie. 
tatia podała sprawę do sądu i w stycznu 2018 wygrała proces. wyrokiem sądu otrzymać miała zadośćuczynienie w wysokości 2 tys. lari.

ramishvili oczywiście nie przyznawał się do winy.

a jakże!

tatia mówi, że problem był dużo większy. naraziła się na potężny ostracyzm społeczny.
w gruzji dyskryminacja płci jest czymś, niestety, oczywistym.

dziś otrzymałam od niej informację, że wygrała sprawę w  sądzie apelacyjnym. 
co prawda nie ma żadnego zapisu w gruzinskim prawie, dotyczącego molestowania.

miejmy nadzieję, że niebawem będzie!

w 2016 nie było jeszcze akcji #metoo. natomiast sytuacja tatii doskonale się q to wpisuje!

gilocav tatia!!!! p.s.

historię tatii będziecie mogli przeczytać jesienią!

text:
//
forget fear first 
then show failure 
the way out /

don't run from your 
sadness, it'll stay anyways /
don't you know - 
everything you run from, 
chases you at a 
greater pace /

broken bones, 
broken homes, 
they're all screaming my 
name , i know /

but i can't return for 
ahead is the only 
direction i now know /
i know it hurts to hurt, 
when everyone is trying to 
save you /
but the hurt is a river 
without a mouth, 
his do you push it back? 
tell me about your losses, 
i'll tell you about my 
victories /
tell me you lost your moon, 
i'll tell you i went out 
looking for the sun /
look you miseries in the eye, 
tell them you're coming back
to take everything you 
left behind / to take back a heart 
that forgot its way home. 
don't run from the hurt, 
it is here only 
to have its share of your heart.
.
.
utopiangrey.
(@utopiangrey)
.
.
.

text_retweet:
repost @realkombucha 
such a great quote, it's so so so true. it's awful for a recovering alcoholic that is open and honest about the dangers of alcohol. people think it's acceptable to tell me that i should go to a meeting and generally rude to me when i choose wellness even when i tell them i went to rehab. it's so crazy how alcohol dominates everything 
the first work conferences i attended sober i was still shy about it and there was no water or non alcoholic drinks available so now i am much more vocal about how unacceptable it is to have no other option. for me this actually worked out well and i was happy to have non alcoholic drinks available at the last event!
at the end of my life i will not remember the years i wasted trying to drink away my problems and anxiety. instead i will be thankful for the rest of my life i learned how to thrive in life without numbing myself so other people are comfortable. when i see alcohol now i see pain and suffering, not the glamorous false lies that are sold to us

text: one of my favorite reads this month (and all of 2018) was “brave” by rose mcgowan. in this book rose talks about how she went from being born into a cult and how she ended up in another cult, hollywood. she talks about surviving a world where victims, specifically women, are molded to be victims by a patriarchal world. she talks about her experiences and holds nothing back. this book moved me completely. i have never felt so seen and heard and understood and that kind of connection is worth shouting about. 100% recommend for anyone who has been a victim of the world they live in, anyone who wants to understand how women feel and are treated, and anyone who loves rose mcgowan’s work and activism as much as i do. i cannot stop thinking about it. absolute favorite memoir ever. ❓who is an author you connected to? 🥀 #brave #rosearmy #rosemcgowan #metoo #bookreccomendation #memoir #books #activism
name: JOHNNA LAFAITH | ohio

text:
.
instagram rewind 2018: итоги года
🔻
instagram выпустил обзор тенденций платформы за 2018 год: чем жило сообщество социальной сети в уходящем году.
🔻
самым популярным стикером в stories стал heart love от arata, а самым часто используемым фильтром для лица — heart eyes. в ленте эмодзи «сердце»  встречалось в комментариях более 14 миллиардов раз.
🔻
что касается интересов аудитории, то в этом году продолжали расти в популярности фото и видео, которые вызывают приятные до мурашек ощущения (asmr): например, резка мыла.
🔻
в игре fortnite также наблюдается взрывной рост: #fortnite — очень быстро набирающий популярность хэштег. крупнейший конкурс вирусного танца года также проходил в instagram — это #inmyfeelingschallenge.
🔻
миллионы людей использовали instagram для того, чтобы их голоса были услышаны. основными пропагандистскими хэштегами года были #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k). это демонстрирует, что instagram можно использовать для того, чтобы высказать свою точку зрения на важные вещи.
🔻
краткие итоги 2018 года:
▪️наиболее используемый фильтр для лица: heart eyes
▪️самый популярный стикер: heart love от arata
▪️количество комментариев: 14 миллиардов
▪️самое счастливое место в мире: диснейленд токио
▪️главная тенденция: asmr
самый быстрорастущий хэштег: #fortnite
▪️самое топовое сообщество: bts (#btsarmy)
▪️самый популярный челлендж: #inmyfeelingschallenge
топовые пропагандистские хэштеги: #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k)

text:
//this poem is written in the point of view of a victim and is not personal to the writer//
my take on the #metoo movement. 
i remember being excited at the thought of this movement kicking off in india. i thought it would be the start of a new era of 0 tolerance. i was to be disappointed it seems. it's disgusting how the first response of the media is to criticise those strong women who were able to come forward and discover the so called "hidden intentions." while there may be crooks in every subject, you should at least be sensitive about the ones who have actually faced trauma. one of the women in my dance class told, "it's disgusting when these old women come forward. if these college girls come forward it's okay." i was appalled to say the least. this is why victims of harassment and even rape never come forward. this poem was written in the point of view of one such woman who was unable to come forward. 
poem and pictures by @xadithix

text:
el joven que acusó al actor kevin spacey de haberle agredido sexualmente en una localidad turística cerca de boston en 2016 filmó parte de la agresión, según la demanda obtenida por la afp.

el actor estadounidense, de 59 años, estrella de la serie "house of cards" y ganador de dos oscar, será acusado formalmente ante el tribunal de la isla de nantucket el 7 de enero de "agresión sexual con lesiones a una persona de más de 14 años". si es reconocido culpable podría ser sentenciado a una pena máxima de cinco años de cárcel.

el joven, identificado como william little y de 18 años en el momento de la presunta agresión, la noche del 7 al 8 de julio de 2016, contó a la policía que envió mensajes vía snapchat, entre ellos un video, a su compañera desde el bar-restaurante "club car" de nantucket, donde se encontraba con el actor, según la demanda.

tras haberse presentado a la estrella y haber aparentado tener 23 años -hace falta tener 21 para beber alcohol en el estado de massachusetts- comenzó a beber con él, primero cerveza y luego whisky.

habría sido entonces cuando el actor puso su mano sobre su pantalón y le tocó el sexo, según la demanda.

little intentó retirar a spacey, al tiempo que intercambiaba mensajes con su compañera sobre la agresión y, como ella no le creía, le envió un video del actor metiendo la mano en su pantalón, video que la policía parece haber encontrado y mostrado al joven, que confirmó que las imágenes eran, efectivamente, las de spacey y él.

i’m learning that even if i react, it won’t change anything...it won’t make people suddenly love and respect me...it won’t magically change their minds. 
sometimes it’s better to just let things be. 
i’ve learned that life is better lived when it’s not centered around what’s happening around me, but instead focused on what’s happening inside of me. 
my joy comes from working on myself and my own inner peace.

text:
weak. lost for words. hopeless. 
i kept my secret of sexual abuse from family and friends so i was utterly alone.

the pain seemed constant and never ending. no one knew what i was experiencing and how i felt. no one to comfort me or console me. no one to cry with. no one to pray with.

each day i tried to convince myself that i could get over it. that i was strong enough to handle it. but the truth is, i was a helpless child.

i’d watch my grandmother pray, so i decided at an early age i would pray. although i didn’t have a relationship with the lord, i figured if grandma prayed, maybe prayer would work for me too.

prayer was my only hope.

hope that one day the pain and torment would end. 
i spent years praying a short prayer, ”help me”. those two words were all that i could muster up.

now i know, for believers two words are all that is needed in our time of weakness. for we have a great intercessor who can articulate and describe what we feel and need perfectly! “in the same way the spirit also helps our weakness; for we do not know how to pray as we should, but the spirit himself intercedes for us with groanings too deep for words;” romans‬ ‭8:26‬ ‭

text:
after a hiatus, we are eager to finally have our annual haiku year-in-review (hyir) out in the world!~
.
the hyir is a review, reflection, a collaborative timepiece to honor the past year in poetry. ~
.
the editors (miller oberman [ @millerwolf8 ], gabrielle bates [ @gabrielle_bates_ ], elizabeth bradfield [ @e.bradfield ], clayre benzadon [ @clayrebenz ], and alexandra teague [ @alexandra.teague ])
have come together to write about a specific event that stood out to them: ~
.
the us/mexico border wall debate, the shooting at the temple of life in squirrel hill, california wildfires, the 2018 un intergovernmental panel on climate change report, and the ford-kavanaugh hearing (and greater #metoo movement). ~
.
enjoy and please be sure to spread this widely!
.
.
.

text_retweet:
ladies, look at where we are and how far we’ve come. let’s take a minute to collectively be grateful for all of the insane battles women have fought for us. we are grateful for the strength we have galvanized to find our voices on every platform, every corner, and from every direction.

we are still fighting for reproductive rights, and also fighting to maintain ownership of our sexuality every day. this is related to the current shortage of sex ed in the u.s. (only 13 out of 50 states require sex education to be medically accurate). women bear the responsibility to educate themselves and each other because of this shortage in education resources. that responsibility weighs more heavily now than ever, with organizations like planned parenthood under threat. with sexual education comes sexual health, and part of that education is self-exploration. in this post, amara purlle explores how the #metoo movement has changed attitudes or heightened recognition of the freedom to explore our bodies as we see fit.

text:
i am strong - what does this mean to you? ⠀
* ⠀
i love my morning session of yoga with adriene. today as a did yoga for teens (yup totally a teenager in my heart 😂 ), adriene finished with thoughts on what it means to be strong. she said: strength looks and feels like many different things. many different flavours. it’s not always ‘roar’ 💪 strong can mean centred, at peace, balanced. ⠀
*⠀
this is so true. we often confuse feeling strong with being mentally and physically tough. sometimes our greatest strength comes from the moments when we accept that it is okay to not be okay. ⠀
*⠀
wishing you all so much peace, laughter, harmony and love⠀
namaste my friends 🙏⠀
*⠀
*⠀
*⠀
